3. The Preſence of CHRIST in a Houſe of publick Worſhip renders it glorious, as it renders the Sacraments there adminiſtred, pleaſant, deſirable and beneficial. The Sacraments of Chriſts Inſtitution, are Baptiſm and the Lord's Supper. Theſe are uſually to be adminiſtred in Publick, in places ſet apart for God's worſhip; but the
influence and the efficacy, the benefit and advantage of them, depends upon Chriſt's Spirit • ere. The Baptiſm of Water will not of it • elf waſh away Sin: That muſt be done by the • enewing of the Holy Ghoſt, or elſe the Ordinance will be ineffectual. So the ſpiritual benefit and advantage of the Lord's Supper, is owing to the Preſence of the Lord there▪ His Bleſſing and gracious Preſence there, renders the Ordinance effectual, for the comforting and edifying the body of Chriſt, till we all come in the unity of the faith and of the knowlege of the Son of God, unto a perfect man, to the meaſure of the ſtature of the fulneſs of Chriſt. This renders it pleaſant & deſirable, as well as advantagious and beneficial. To Sit at the Table of the Lord, this cauſes his People to ſit under his ſhadow with great delight▪ and makes his fruit ſweet to their taſte. They are refreſhed edified and comforted by it, and improved in their fitneſs for Heavenly Glory▪ Here they receive ſome foretaſts of the inexpreſſible pleaſure of Communion with Chriſt. This ſtrengthens their hands and encourages their hearts to be ſledfaſt & unmoveable, always to abound in the work of the Lord; and cauſes them to wax ſtronger and ſtronger in the Lord and in the power of his Might, and to grow brighter and brighter Ornaments of Chriſt's Church;
like thoſe the Pſalmiſt ſpeaks of, that are planted in the houſe of the Lord, They will flouriſh in the courts of our God, they'll bring forth fruit in old age, Pſal. 92. 13, 14.
